page.title: 01WILDLIFE PART ONE.
page.content:
{ { {CARNOCK MOOR}
We found a tree which held a squirrels drey. It was a mass of twigs and dried leaves which gave a lot of camouflage. Below the tree lay cones with the seeds eaten by squirrels. Later on we saw a hole that men dug for a hideout. After the scent of the men had gone foxes moved in and lived in the hole. When they left a family of rabbits moved in. We walked on until we found some rabbit or chicken bones. They were beside three big foxes dens. The foxes could catch rabbits deeper in the forest or steal chickens from the nearby chicken farm. {We felt out of place in the forest and {felt like everything was watching us.
